<Layouts.app flash={@flash}>
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-16 py-8">
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <h1 class="pb-4 text-5xl font-bold">
        Hello!
      </h1>

      <h1 class="text-7xl font-semibold">
        My name is <span class="bg-linear-to-r from-violet-500 via-purple-400 to-fuchsia-500 bg-clip-text font-extrabold text-transparent">Nathan Whyte</span>,
      </h1>

      <p class="text-3xl">it's a pleasure to meet you. <span>üëãüèª</span></p>
    </section>

    <section class="flex flex-row gap-4 lg:gap-16">
      <div class="max-w-52 float-left block text-center">
        <div class="avatar">
          <div class="size-52 rounded-md">
            <img src={~p"/images/Headshot.png"} alt="Nathan Whyte" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex max-w-5xl flex-col gap-4 text-xl">
        <p class="text-2xl font-medium">
          I'm a <span class="font-bold text-purple-400">Full Stack Software Engineer</span>
          based in weird and wonderful <span class="font-bold text-amber-700">Austin, Texas</span>. ü§òüèª
        </p>

        <p class="text-2xl">
          I'm passionate about working all across the stack, from <span class="font-bold text-purple-300">creating smooth, user-friendly UIs</span>,
          to <span class="font-bold text-violet-500">building performant backend APIs</span>,
          all the way to <span class="font-bold text-fuchsia-400">deploying scalable services to the cloud</span>.
        </p>

        <p>
          I love solving problems of all kinds, even the ones that keep me up late.
        </p>

        <%!-- TODO: update the links, then to cards with links --%>
        <p class="block">
          Find me on
          <Layouts.link_button
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nathan-whyte/"
            label="LinkedIn"
            icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
            target="_blank"
          /> and
          <Layouts.link_button
            href="https://github.com/nathanwhyte"
            label="GitHub"
            icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
            target="_blank"
          />
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h1 class=" col-span-full py-4 text-4xl font-medium">
        Projects
      </h1>

      <div class="grid auto-rows-auto gap-4 lg:gap-4 xl:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-violet-950/15 flex h-full flex-col space-y-4 rounded-md border border-violet-950 p-6">
          <Layouts.project_card_header>
            <:title>
              <.icon name="hero-star-micro" class="size-8 text-fuchsia-500" /> üêã
              <span class="font-bold">Kubernetes Homelab</span>
            </:title>
            <:actions>
              <%!-- <Layouts.link_button href="/" label="Stats" icon="hero-arrow-down-micro" /> --%>
              <Layouts.link_button
                href="https://github.com/nathanwhyte/homelab"
                label="GitHub"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />
            </:actions>
          </Layouts.project_card_header>

          <p>
            My self-hosted
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://docs.k3s.io/"
              label="K3s"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> Kubernetes cluster running on 4 Ubuntu Linux nodes.
          </p>

          <p>
            The cluster hosts web applications, databases, an image registry, and much more.
          </p>
          Notable services include:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              A
              <Layouts.inline_link_button
                href="https://goharbor.io/"
                label="Harbor"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              /> image registry used by many of the services running in the cluster.
            </li>
            <li>
              Persistent storage via
              <Layouts.inline_link_button
                href="https://longhorn.io/"
                label="Longhorn"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />, which has already prevented a few different data loss scares.
            </li>
            <li>
              A logs and monitoring stack powered by
              <Layouts.inline_link_button
                href="https://grafana.com/oss/grafana/?plcmt=oss-nav"
                label="Grafana OSS"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />,
              <Layouts.inline_link_button
                href="https://grafana.com/oss/prometheus/?plcmt=oss-nav"
                label="Loki"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />, and
              <Layouts.inline_link_button
                href="https://prometheus.io/"
                label="Prometheus"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />.
            </li>
            <li>This very website!</li>
          </ul>

          <p>For more details, of which there are many, check the GitHub repository.</p>

          <div class="flex grow items-end">
            <p class="text-purple-fg/75 text-sm italic">
              It's like AWS, if AWS was way cheaper and hosted entirely from my office next to my cat's food bowl
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-violet-950/15 flex h-full flex-col space-y-4 rounded-md border border-violet-950 p-6">
          <Layouts.project_card_header>
            <:title>
              ü™ù <span class="font-bold">Build Hook</span>
            </:title>
            <:actions>
              <Layouts.link_button
                href="https://github.com/nathanwhyte/build-hook"
                label="GitHub"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />
            </:actions>
          </Layouts.project_card_header>

          <p>
            My CI/CD solution, replacing building images and deploying services entirely within GitHub Actions runners.
          </p>
          Instead, I just call a endpoint hosted within my homelab cluster that:
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Pulls the latest code from the configured GitHub repository</li>
            <li>
              Kicks off a build process using Docker's
              <span class="bg-violet-800/25 rounded-sm border border-violet-800 px-1 py-0.5 text-sm">
                buildx
              </span>
              Kubernetes driver
            </li>
            <li>Restarts the specified Kubernetes services after builds are finished</li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            Build Hook is implemented using Rust's
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://docs.rs/axum/latest/axum/"
              label="Axum"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> web framework, with configuration defined using
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://toml.io/en/"
              label="TOML"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            />.
          </p>

          <div class="flex grow items-end">
            <p class="text-purple-fg/75 grow text-sm italic">
              I'll be stashing my GitHub Actions savings for a rainy DevOps day (any time I build a Next.js image)
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-violet-950/15 flex h-full flex-col space-y-4 rounded-md border border-violet-950 p-6">
          <Layouts.project_card_header>
            <:title>
              üß† <span class="font-bold">Glossary</span>
            </:title>
            <:actions>
              <Layouts.link_button
                href="https://github.com/nathanwhyte/glossary"
                label="GitHub"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />
            </:actions>
          </Layouts.project_card_header>

          <p>
            A knowledge base, notes store, and personal wiki made to contend with my ADHD-riddled brain.
          </p>

          <p>
            Integrated search engine for keyword searches, tag and topic filtering, and project organization.
          </p>

          <p>
            Written in
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://www.elixir-lang.org/"
              label="Elixir"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> and built using
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://www.phoenixframework.org/"
              label="Phoenix LiveView"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> for reactivity, with
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://tailwindcss.com/"
              label="Tailwind CSS"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> for styling.
          </p>

          <div class="flex grow items-end">
            <p class="text-purple-fg/75 grow text-sm italic">
              Google's worst nightmare, if it was still the 90s
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-violet-950/15 flex h-full flex-col space-y-4 rounded-md border border-violet-950 p-6">
          <Layouts.project_card_header>
            <:title>
              <.icon name="hero-star-micro" class="size-8 text-fuchsia-500" /> üìà
              <span class="font-bold">Equal Risk Portfolio Calculator</span>
            </:title>
            <:actions>
              <Layouts.link_button
                href="https://github.com/nathanwhyte/equal-risk-portfolio"
                label="GitHub"
                icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
                target="_blank"
              />
            </:actions>
          </Layouts.project_card_header>

          <p>
            Assists financial adviors over at
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://targetedwealthsolutions.com/"
              label="Targeted Wealth Solutions"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            />
            in calculating risk-weighted stock allocations in their portfolios, allowing them to consistently outperform the S&P 500.
          </p>

          <p>
            Stock ticker search and real-time stock data using the
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://massive.com/"
              label="Massive"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> <i>(formerly Polygon)</i>
            REST API.
          </p>

          <p>
            Frotnend and primary backend services built using
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://rubyonrails.org/"
              label="Ruby on Rails"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            />, with a Python math engine managed by
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://docs.astral.sh/uv/"
              label="uv"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> running
            <Layouts.inline_link_button
              href="https://pandas.pydata.org/"
              label="Pandas"
              icon="hero-arrow-top-right-on-square-micro"
              target="_blank"
            /> for calculations.
          </p>

          <div class="flex grow items-end">
            <p class="text-purple-fg/75 grow text-sm italic">
              "Money trees is the perfect place for shade, and that's just how I feel..."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

